markdown.markdown:
I am a PhD student in **ecotoxicology and environmental chemistry**, investigating the toxicity of both untreated and *advanced oxidation-processed* nanoplastics and microplastics—whether alone or in combination with emerging co-contaminants—on aquatic organisms such as *Daphnia magna* and *Chlamydomonas reinhardtii*. Additionally, I manage data processing, visualization and produce visually engaging reports using Quarto.



Simply put, **ecotoxicology** is the study of how contaminants affect living beings, from the molecular level to entire ecosystems.<br>
To do this, I use organisms that I cultivate in the lab, expose them to contaminants, and observe what happens.

```{=html}
<div class="organism-container wide">
  <div class="organism-image slide-in-left">
    <img src="photos/daphnia_magna.png"
         alt="Beautiful image of Daphnia magna"
         style="width:300px; height:auto;" />
  </div>
  <div class="organism-text fade-in">
    <h2><em>Daphnia magna</em></h2>
    <p>
      As a primary consumer in freshwater, <em>Daphnia magna</em> is transparent—ideal for observing morphological changes and pollutant sensitivity.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
```

```{=html}
<div class="organism-container wide reverse">
  <div class="organism-text fade-in">
    <h2><em>Chlamydomonas reinhardtii</em></h2>
    <p>
      At the base of the trophic chain, <em>Chlamydomonas reinhardtii</em> 
      is a primary producer. It is highly sensitive and grows rapidly, making it ideal for ecotoxicology 
      studies.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="organism-image slide-in-right">
    <img src="photos/chlamy_1.png"
         alt="Beautiful image of Chlamydomonas reinhardtii"
         style="max-width: 300px; width: 100%; height: auto;" />
  </div>
</div>
```

```{=html}
<script>
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
  // Select all elements with animation classes
  const animatedElements = document.querySelectorAll('.slide-in-left, .slide-in-right, .fade-in');

  // Create an Intersection Observer with a threshold of 50%
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries, observer) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.add('in-view');
        // Stop observing once animation has been triggered
        observer.unobserve(entry.target);
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.5 });

  // Observe each animated element
  animatedElements.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
});
</script>
```

